  "prompt": "What are the Indian petrol pump scams that everyone needs to be warned about?",
  "response": "Here are some common petrol pump scams in India:\n\n1. Meter Tampering\n- Rigged fuel meters that show more fuel dispensed than actually filled\n- Partially adjusted digital/analog meters to overcharge customers\n\n2. Short Filling\n- Deliberately not filling complete requested amount\n- Using techniques to show less fuel has been dispensed\n\n3. Card/Digital Payment Fraud\n- Adding extra charges during digital transactions\n- Charging multiple times for single transaction\n\n4. Fake/Duplicate Billing\n- Creating duplicate bills with inflated amounts\n- Charging extra amounts not reflected in actual fuel quantity\n\n5. Weight/Volume Manipulation\n- Using temperature variations to reduce actual fuel quantity\n- Adjusting dispensing nozzles to release less fuel\n\n6. Cash Transaction Tricks\n- Not providing complete change\n- Creating confusion during cash payments\n\nPrevention Tips:\n- Always check/verify fuel meter reading\n- Request printed bill\n- Watch fuel dispensing carefully\n- Use digital payment modes\n- Check fuel quantity before leaving\n- Report suspicious activities\n\nThese scams are widespread, and consumers should remain vigilant to protect themselves from potential fraud at petrol pumps.",
